# Application root Kconfig for uwb_tag_firmware.
#
# Zephyr's CMake module (cmake/modules/kconfig.cmake) automatically promotes
# this file to KCONFIG_ROOT when it is present in APPLICATION_SOURCE_DIR,
# replacing the default $(ZEPHYR_BASE)/Kconfig.  This file therefore MUST
# source the Zephyr tree first so that all board/SoC/kernel symbols are still
# defined.
#
# Application-specific symbols are sourced after the Zephyr tree.

source "$(ZEPHYR_BASE)/Kconfig"

# DW1000 UWB transceiver driver (vendored Decawave API)
source "$(APPLICATION_SOURCE_DIR)/drivers/dw1000/Kconfig"

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Tag power-management profile (ADR-0046, UWB-314)
#
# "LocationTag" is a low-power *profile* of the single tag app, not a forked
# app/board (ADR-0046 "Decision"). This symbol is the switch; what it
# actually changes lives in overlay-lowpower.conf, layered on top of
# prj.conf by CMakeLists.txt (EXTRA_CONF_FILE) whenever this is set — see
# that file's header comment for the settings themselves and why they live
# in a .conf fragment rather than Kconfig `default`/`select` overrides here
# (the board's own nrf52dk_nrf52832_defconfig assigns real values to several
# of the symbols involved, which outranks any conditional Kconfig default).
#
# Bench/debug builds (this symbol left at its default, n) are unaffected:
# RTT + UART logging and always-on BLE advertising are unchanged.
#
# Out of scope here (later UWB-13 subissues, ADR-0046 "New work created"):
# DW1000 sleep/wake (UWB-316), the STANDBY state machine (UWB-319),
# BLE-advertising duty-cycle policy (UWB-320), battery monitoring (UWB-322).
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

config UWB_TAG_LOW_POWER
	bool "Low-power tag profile (ADR-0046 'LocationTag')"
	default n
	help
	  Enables the field/low-power operating profile described in ADR-0046
	  (docs/adr/0046-tag-power-management-profile.md, FUNDAMENTALS_SPORTS
	  repo): CONFIG_PM_DEVICE plus dropping the RTT/UART log backends (and
	  the UART console) that would otherwise hold the CPU and peripherals
	  awake, and a lower default log level. See overlay-lowpower.conf for
	  the exact settings.

	  NOTE — CONFIG_PM (system-level power-state residency policy) is NOT
	  enabled by this symbol: on the pinned NCS v2.7.0 / Zephyr 3.6.99 tree
	  this repo builds against, no Nordic SoC (nRF52/53/91/54) `select`s
	  HAS_PM, so CONFIG_PM has no satisfiable path to y on nrf52dk_nrf52832
	  (verified locally — `select PM` here fails Kconfig's dependency
	  check). Zephyr's tickless kernel (CONFIG_TICKLESS_KERNEL, default y
	  when TICKLESS_CAPABLE) and the Cortex-M idle loop's WFE/WFI already
	  give event-driven CPU idle between radio events without CONFIG_PM;
	  CONFIG_PM would only add SoC-level residency-state *policy* on top,
	  which this SoC port does not implement in this Zephyr version.
	  CONFIG_PM_DEVICE (device suspend/resume hooks, used by the DW1000
	  sleep seam, UWB-316) has no such dependency and is enabled normally.

	  Leave at the default (n) for bench/debug builds.

	  This is the build-profile + PM-baseline mechanism only (UWB-314). It
	  does not implement the STANDBY state machine, DW1000 sleep/wake, BLE
	  advertising duty-cycling, or battery monitoring — those are separate
	  UWB-13 subissues (UWB-316/319/320/322) that build on this seam.
